97
00:04:04.901 --> 00:04:06.437
It's the idea that the brain is embedded

98
00:04:06.437 --> 00:04:07.460
in the nervous system.

99
00:04:07.460 --> 00:04:08.453
So when I talk about the brain,

100
00:04:08.453 --> 00:04:10.436
I'm really talking about the nervous system,

101
00:04:10.436 --> 00:04:11.812
which is embedded in the body,

102
00:04:11.812 --> 00:04:13.337
intertwining with all these other systems,

103
00:04:13.337 --> 00:04:15.194
the immune system, the reproductive systems,

104
00:04:15.194 --> 00:04:16.495
all those systems.

105
00:04:16.495 --> 00:04:18.692
And then it's embedded in nature altogether,

106
00:04:18.692 --> 00:04:20.579
and in culture, across time.

107
00:04:20.579 --> 00:04:24.537
So in that broad, interdependent, interconnected view,

108
00:04:24.537 --> 00:04:26.435
which is very consistent with modern science

109
00:04:26.435 --> 00:04:30.241
both in terms of quantum physics, and deep ecology,

110
00:04:30.241 --> 00:04:32.835
as well as the post-modern view of culture.

111
00:04:32.835 --> 00:04:35.340
Inside all of that, this system,

112
00:04:35.340 --> 00:04:36.962
now I'll just talk about the brain,

113
00:04:36.962 --> 00:04:38.423
moves information around.

114
00:04:38.423 --> 00:04:40.077
In other words, it sends signals.

115
00:04:40.077 --> 00:04:42.060
So the brain moves information around

116
00:04:42.060 --> 00:04:44.237
like your heart moves blood around.

117
00:04:44.237 --> 00:04:46.741
And each little bit of information

118
00:04:47.501 --> 00:04:49.344
conveys meaning in some way.

119
00:04:49.344 --> 00:04:51.956
Now most of those meanings are at a very, very basic level,

120
00:04:51.956 --> 00:04:54.773
like tracking the amount of blood flow

121
00:04:54.773 --> 00:04:57.130
in the lower intestine, or something like that.

122
00:04:57.130 --> 00:05:01.172
But layered up, increasingly higher and higher up,

123
00:05:01.172 --> 00:05:03.647
which also maps to how the brain evolved

124
00:05:03.647 --> 00:05:06.985
over evolutionary time, you know, 600 million years,

125
00:05:06.985 --> 00:05:10.472
roughly, of the evolution of the nervous system.

126
00:05:11.292 --> 00:05:13.757
At the higher levels, the brain is moving

127
00:05:13.757 --> 00:05:15.356
so much information around

128
00:05:15.356 --> 00:05:17.778
at such a sophisticated and integrated way,

129
00:05:17.778 --> 00:05:19.217
that we can actually have a sense

130
00:05:19.217 --> 00:05:21.876
of understanding each other right here and now.

131
00:05:22.821 --> 00:05:25.284
The net of it is that the mind, as I define it,

132
00:05:25.284 --> 00:05:28.206
is the flow of information through the nervous system.

133
00:05:28.206 --> 00:05:31.001
Most of that information is forever unconscious,

134
00:05:31.001 --> 00:05:34.040
but the two are intertwined, mind and brain,

135
00:05:34.040 --> 00:05:37.101
in that as the brain changes, the mind changes.

136
00:05:37.101 --> 00:05:38.359
<v Regina>Yeah, let's talk about that,</v>

137
00:05:38.359 --> 00:05:41.260
how the mind also changes the brain.

138
00:05:41.260 --> 00:05:45.260
<v ->Right, well, for example, just as information flows</v>

139
00:05:45.260 --> 00:05:46.455
through the nervous system,

140
00:05:46.455 --> 00:05:48.042
'cause that's what the mind is,

141
00:05:48.042 --> 00:05:51.436
what that does is literally change the brain

142
00:05:51.436 --> 00:05:52.481
in a variety of ways.

143
00:05:52.481 --> 00:05:55.670
For example, parts of the brain that are more active

144
00:05:55.670 --> 00:05:57.342
have more blood flow.

145
00:05:57.342 --> 00:06:00.137
Synapses that fire, or neurons that fire frequently

146
00:06:00.137 --> 00:06:02.675
become more sensitive to simulation.

147
00:06:02.675 --> 00:06:04.275
There's a famous saying in neurology,

148
00:06:04.275 --> 00:06:07.095
"Neurons that fire together wire together."

149
00:06:07.095 --> 00:06:09.073
It's pretty mechanical at a basic level.

150
00:06:09.073 --> 00:06:11.973
In other words, the more neurons that are firing,

151
00:06:11.973 --> 00:06:13.606
and the longer they're firing,

152
00:06:13.606 --> 00:06:15.504
and the more intensively they're firing,

153
00:06:15.504 --> 00:06:19.097
the better they get in terms of wiring together.

154
00:06:19.097 --> 00:06:21.571
Lots of really fun studies show this sort of thing.

155
00:06:21.571 --> 00:06:24.590
One of my favorite are taxi cab drivers in London.

156
00:06:24.590 --> 00:06:25.070
<v Regina>Yes.</v>

157
00:06:25.070 --> 00:06:27.395
<v ->They have to memorize the twisty, turny streets there.</v>

158
00:06:27.395 --> 00:06:29.325
They're hippocampus, a part of the brain

159
00:06:29.325 --> 00:06:32.206
that's involved in visual-spacial memory, is thicker.

160
00:06:32.206 --> 00:06:35.832
Literally, measurably thicker at the end of their training

161
00:06:35.832 --> 00:06:37.632
than it was at the beginning of their training,

162
00:06:37.632 --> 00:06:41.771
because all that mental activity of memorizing streets,

163
00:06:41.771 --> 00:06:44.715
has actually forged new neural structures.

